== Sugar 2.0
-- To-do


Tools
=====

- `ctags-like` wrapper
- syntax highlighting for many editors

Syntax 
======

Incompatible changes
--------------------

Inline conditionals::

	currently

	```
	if CONDITION -> EXPRESSION (| CONDITION -> EXPRESSION)* | EXPRESSION
	```

	better would be 

	```
	CONDITION ? EXPRESSION : EXPRESSION
	```

	or 

	```
	EXPRESSION if CONDITION else EXPRESSION
	```

Remove mandatory ends::

	At the end of the day, they don't serve any real purpose besides
	guarding against copy-paste.

New features
------------

Comments in maps/lists::

	```
	{
		value: 1 # Some comment
		# value: 1 -- Value commented out
	}
	```

Multi-line strings::

	```
	# Just like in Python
	"""asdsads
	asdsadas"""
	```

	```
	let a = """
	string on 
	multiple lines
	"""

	if c:
		let b = """
		string
		on 
		multiple
		lines
		"""
	```

String format/interpolation::


	We could use inline expressions

	```
	f"{some code}, {1 + 2}" 
	```

	Or format with positional arguments

	```
	"{0:d} {1:d}" % ()     # Uses the local scope
	"{0:d} {1:d}" % {dict} # Uses the given dict as a scope
	```

Tuples::

	```
	(1,2,3,4)
	```

	```
	() 
	(1)
	(1, 2, 3)
	(,) 
	(1,) 
	```

Named tuples::

	```
	(a=1, b=2, c=3, 4)
	```

Primitive alternative constructors::

	```
	[1,2,3,4]@AltClass
	```

Chaining::

	```
	d3 selection () 
		a ()          # a is called on the result of d3 selection ()
		b ()          # b is called on the result of ()

	d3 selection () :
		a ()          # both a and b are with the same result
		b ()
	```

	```
	value:
		a ()
		b ()
	```
	
	is equal to

	```
	value a () b ()
	```

	and you can also affect that

	```
	var r = value:
		a ()
		b ()
	```

	and chain it

	```
	var r = value:
		a ()
		b () :
			c ()
	```
	
	which equals to

	```
	var r = value ()
	r a ()
	var t = r b ()
	t c ()
	```


Pattern matching::

	as a keyword

	```
	match getResult()
		<string>
			"A string"
		<number> and _ > 10	
			"A number"
		<number> and _ < 0	
			"A negative number"
		*
			"Rest"
	end
	```

	as a specific chain type

	```
	expression |
		predicate
			block
		predicate â†’ line
		<type>
	```

	alternate syntax:

	```
	match value as f
		case 1.0
			code
		case f like (_, _, _)
			code
		else
			code
	end
	```

Decorators::

	```
	@function decorate f, a
		f __value = a
		return f
	@end

	@function pouet
	@decorate 10
	```
	
Absence of value::

	```
	var a = (asdas sadasd ? {})
	```

Setdefault::

	```
	var a = {}
	a ["asdsa" ?= {}]["pouet"] = 10
	```

Hex/Bit notation::

	```
	0xFF
	0b011010101
	```

Bit-logic operator::
	
	```
	&&
	||
	!
	```

Infix operator::

	```
	e ~map extractor 
	```

	would be rewritten as

	```
	map (e, extractor)
	```

 Infix functions::
 
 	@infix @function fold XXXX fold XXXX -> fold (XXX,XXX)

Like operation::
	
	v like (_, _, _)

	like takes a structural expression that will tell if the left-hand value
	is "like" the right hand value

List comprehensions / generators::

	 [x * 2 for x in COLLECTION if CONDITION]
	 (x * 2 for x in COLLECTION if CONDITION)

Select/match::


Streamlined mappings::

	_ :: connector Project fold :: {_| (group[_ discipline [-1]] ?= []) push (_)}

Design-by-contract Assert/pre/post/error::	

	@function f
	@pre   expresssion error message
	@post  expression  error message
		body
	@where
		Test case
	@end

Dictionary setdefault/assign if not null::

	a[1] ?= 1.0
	
	equals to

	if not isDefined(a[1]) -> a[1] = 1.0


Generators::

	```
	var f = {
		for a in 0..100
			yield a
		end
	}
	```

Special variables::

	```
	__scope_name__ (ex: widgets.Widget.ensure)
	__scope__ 

	__module__
	__module_name__

	__class__
	__class_name__

	__method__
	__method_name__

	__function__
	__function_name__

	__class__
	__class_name__

	__line__
	__file__
	```


	and so in code


	```
	error ("{__scope_name__}:{__line__}: Error message")
	```


Named arguments::
	
	```
	@function i a, b, rest...
	@end
	```

	```
	@function i a, b, rest..., options=...
	@end
	```

Macros::

	```
	@macro name( a, b, c )
		$a = pouet
		$b = pouet
		$c = pouet
	@end

	@function f
		@name(a,b,c)
	@end
	```

	will produce the code $a, $b, $c

	```
	@function f
		a = pouet
		b = pouet
		c = pouet
	@end
	```

Implemented
===========

Default arguments::

	```
	@function f a=0, b=1, c=2
	@end
	```

Automatic variables::

	```
	_  == arguments[0]
	_0 == arguments[0]
	_1 == arguments[1]
	_2 == arguments[2]
	```

Implicit return::

	```
	{_| _ + 1}
	```

Continue/break::

	```
	for a,b in 0..10
		if a == 5
			continue
		elif a > 7
			break
		end
	end
	```

Map/filter/... operators::

	```
	Filter  VALUE ::? PREDICATE
	Map     VALUE ::= EXTRACTOR
	Reduce  VALUE ::> EXTRACTOR
	ReduceR VALUE ::< EXTRACTOR
	```

# EOF

